A man was found hanged in the Silverglen Nature Reserve on Thursday, 27 February. Amawele Emergency Services spokesman, Sivan Soobramodey, said: “When paramedics got to the area, they noticed a man hanged upside-down from a tree. The man was declared dead at the scene.”Bayview police said they were awaiting the post-mortem results to determine the cause of death. Warrant Officer Collin Chetty, Bayview SAPS communications officer, said that at this stage, “there is no indication of a murder. Police are awaiting post-mortem results to determine and get clarity with respect of the cause of death,” he said.